  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620230533593-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620230533593-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620230533593-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620230533593-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620230533593-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a pot with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until sizzling</p><p>Once the cumin seeds start to sizzle, carefully add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620230538278-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620230538278-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620230538278-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620230538278-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620230538278-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>turmeric rice</strong></p>",
